A.2 Land Cover Classification Systems Used in India
n National Land Cover Mapping System (NLCMS):
ISRO/NRSC developed a National Land Cover Map of India using IRS Resourcesat imagery at
1:50,000 scale. Covers entire India with 18 Level-I and 50 Level-II classes. Updated every 2 years.
Used for national planning.
n National Land Use Land Cover (LULC) Mapping — SAC, Ahmedabad:
Space Applications Centre (SAC) produces LULC maps at 1:250,000 scale using IRS data. Classifies
into: Agricultural land, Forest, Wasteland, Water bodies, Built-up land, Pasture/Grassland, Barren land.
n Wasteland Atlas of India:
NRSC produces Wasteland Atlas — maps degraded, unused and underutilised land. Identifies: ravines,
gullied land, salt-affected, waterlogged, mining/industrial wastelands. Used for land reclamation
planning.
n National Wetland Atlas:
ISRO/SAC maps all wetlands of India (lakes, ponds, rivers, coastal wetlands) using IRS data. Identifies
Ramsar sites, wetland health, change over time.
n CORINE Land Cover (European):
Coordination of Information on the Environment — EU land cover mapping system. 44 classes at
1:100,000 scale using Sentinel-2. Template for many national systems.
