SECTION C : VEGETATION STUDY
Vegetation monitoring is the most widely used application of remote sensing. Plants have unique spectral
signatures — they absorb red light for photosynthesis and strongly reflect NIR radiation (due to leaf cell
structure). This spectral contrast forms the basis of all vegetation indices.
