C.2 Vegetation Monitoring Applications — India Focus
n Crop Area and Production Estimation (FASAL Project):
FASAL (Forecasting Agricultural output using Space, Agro-meteorology and Land based observations)
is India's operational crop forecasting system by MNCFC (Ministry of Agriculture). Uses IRS AWiFS
(56m), Sentinel-2 (10m) NDVI data to forecast wheat, rice, cotton and other crop areas at district level
— 3 forecasts before harvest. Accuracy: within 5% of actual production.
n Desertification and Land Degradation Atlas:
