ISRO/SAC used IRS data + NDVI trend analysis to map India's desertification extent. Declining NDVI
trend over years = vegetation degradation = desertification indicator. India: ~97 million ha under
degradation (2019).
n Invasive Species Mapping:
Lantana camara (a major forest invasive) mapped in Rajaji Tiger Reserve using hyperspectral data —
its unique spectral signature distinguishes it from native vegetation. Prosopis juliflora (mesquite)
mapped in semi-arid areas of Rajasthan and Gujarat using NDVI anomaly.
n Grassland and Pasture Monitoring:
Grassland NDVI time series from MODIS tracks forage availability. Useful for nomadic pastoralists,
wildlife managers and drought early warning in Rajasthan, Gujarat, Himalayan alpine meadows.
