SECTION D : FORESTRY APPLICATIONS
Forestry is one of the earliest and most mature application domains of remote sensing. India's Forest
Survey of India (FSI) has been using satellite data since the 1980s to produce its biennial 'State of Forest
Report' (SFR).
D.1 Forest Inventory and Mapping
n Forest Cover Mapping:
Multispectral classification of IRS Resourcesat-2 LISS-III (23.5m) imagery into forest classes: Very
Dense Forest (VDF, canopy density >70%), Moderately Dense Forest (MDF, 40–70%), Open Forest
(OF, 10–40%) and Scrub (<10%). India's total forest cover (2021): 7,13,789 km² = 21.71% of
geographical area. This is from FSI's biennial State of Forest Report.
n Forest Type Mapping:
Distinguish tropical wet evergreen, tropical dry deciduous, temperate coniferous, mangroves,
grasslands etc. using seasonal multi-date imagery (deciduous forests lose leaves in dry season —
detectable by NDVI drop). Champion and Seth's forest type classification used as reference.
n Above-Ground Biomass (AGB) Estimation:
LiDAR-derived canopy height + allometric equations ® biomass. ALOS PALSAR (L-band SAR) also
sensitive to forest biomass. Critical for REDD+ (Reducing Emissions from Deforestation and forest
Degradation) — countries earn carbon credits by proving forest carbon stocks.
n Forest Fragmentation Analysis:
GIS spatial metrics (patch size, edge density, connectivity) quantify how forests are being fragmented
by roads, agriculture, settlements. Fragmentation reduces wildlife corridors and increases edge effects.
Used for wildlife corridor planning and protected area management.
n Growing Stock Volume Estimation:
Combination of field-measured tree diameters (DBH), heights and RS-derived parameters (canopy
cover, NDVI) estimate timber volume. Used by State Forest Departments for sustainable harvest
planning.
D.2 Deforestation and Degradation Monitoring
n Deforestation Detection:
Annual or seasonal comparison of classified forest maps detects areas converted to non-forest. Hansen
et al. Global Forest Watch uses LANDSAT to map deforestation globally at 30m resolution — annual
updates, freely available. India-specific: NRSC monitors forest cover change for each state.
n REDD+ (Reducing Emissions from Deforestation and Forest Degradation):
UN REDD+ programme uses RS+GIS to establish reference emission levels and measure forest
carbon. Countries receive payments for verified forest carbon conservation. India has submitted Forest
Reference Emission Level (FREL) to UNFCCC based on RS data.
UGC NET Environmental Sciences (Code 89) | Unit I – 1.7 | Page 10
n Encroachment Detection in Forest Areas:
High-resolution imagery (Cartosat-2/3, Google Earth) compared with legal forest boundary (GIS data)
identifies encroachments. Used by Forest Departments and courts as evidence.
n Illegal Logging Detection:
Sudden NDVI decline in small patches without official clearance indicates illegal logging. SAR
(Sentinel-1) can detect canopy gaps even under cloud cover — critical in tropical regions.
D.3 Forest Fire Detection and Management
n Active Fire Detection:
MODIS Terra/Aqua satellites detect active fires globally using thermal bands (3.9 mm and 11 mm). Fires
emit strongly at these wavelengths. MODIS provides near-real-time fire alerts (4 times/day with
Terra+Aqua). SNPP VIIRS: 375m resolution — more accurate for small fires. India: Forest Survey of
India and NRSC maintain fire alert portals.
n Burn Severity Mapping (NBR):
NBR = (NIR - SWIR)/(NIR + SWIR). Pre-fire minus post-fire NBR = dNBR. dNBR > 0.66: high severity;
0.44–0.66: moderate-high; 0.1–0.44: low; <0.1: unburned. USGS fire severity classification. Used for
post-fire rehabilitation planning.
n Fire Risk/Susceptibility Mapping:
GIS integration of: dry fuel load (NDVI), slope, aspect, wind direction, road proximity (ignition risk), land
cover ® fire risk zones. Helps pre-position fire-fighting resources.
n Post-Fire Recovery Monitoring:
Time-series NDVI tracks vegetation recovery after fire. Recovery rates differ by vegetation type and fire
severity. Provides data for replanting plans and insurance claims.
